The Department of International Relations and Cooperation
(Dirco) on Wednesday said it had received confirmation from the South African
Consulate General in Dubai that South African businessman Justin van Pletzen
was being detained."It is alleged that Mr Van Pletzen's arrest is linked
to a video he recently circulated about Mr Ajay Gupta, whom he met in Dubai.
However, this is yet to be confirmed by the local authorities,"
spokesperson Ndivhuwo Mabaya said."Consular staff from the mission in Dubai did visit Mr
Van Pletzen [on Wednesday] and Dirco will maintain contact with Mr Van Pletzen
