nature of the charge or when Van Pletzen would appear in court.A friend of Van Pletzen confirmed the arrest to News24 on
Tuesday, while Dirco confirmed that the businessman's mother had made contact
claiming her son had been apprehended.In the recording, Van Pletzen is seen speaking to a relaxed
Ajay Gupta in Dubai, asking him if he would return to South Africa.Gupta appears friendly, and tells Van Pletzen that South
African authorities had not yet given him "a reply"."The day they give a reply, I'll go there," Gupta
added.After the publication of the footage, Hawks spokesperson
Hangwani Mulaudzi said it was up to the investigating officer to find ways to
bring Gupta - who is considered a fugitive from justice - back into the
country.The Hawks have not yet revealed what Gupta is wanted for and
only said that the charges were not related to the Estina Dairy Farm project in
